"{\"uid\": \"www.pymnts.com.-brexit-2016-brexit-bitcoin-and-ethereum-governance-gone-awry-with-beach-reading--Part3\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"for 70 percent of the bitcoin transactions.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 43, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A majority vote by the miners also determines, in effect, how Ethereum will deal with the DAO hack.\", \"from\": 45, \"to\": 144, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"That could decide the long-term fate of the virtual currency platform.\", \"from\": 145, \"to\": 215, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"If you are interested in maximizing the value of a public platform to its participants, giving the decision-making power to one group of participants is not likely to accomplish that objective.\", \"from\": 217, \"to\": 410, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"So letting the miners decide seems obviously wrongheaded.\", \"from\": 411, \"to\": 468, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Making the decision based on the majority of transactions is also dubious since it can allow a small number of large players to dictate the result for all participants.\", \"from\": 469, \"to\": 637, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Brexit, bitcoin, and Ethereum all show the importance of good governance.\", \"from\": 639, \"to\": 712, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Right now, they all seem to be heading off of a cliff, each from insisting on \\\"democratic\\\" voting that most communities, given a choice, decide not to use.\", \"from\": 713, \"to\": 868, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The U.K. actually has a representative democracy in place that could pull it back from the brink.\", \"from\": 869, \"to\": 966, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Bitcoin and Ethereum, unfortunately, have hardwired governance systems that are incapable of maximizing the value of these platforms for their participants.\", \"from\": 967, \"to\": 1123, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Beach Reading  For those of you interested in beach reading, here are some suggestions related to this topic.\", \"from\": 1125, \"to\": 1234, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"My Governing Bad Behavior paper and Chapter 9 of \\\"Matchmakers: The New Economics of Multisided Platforms\\\" provides background on why and how platforms, whether physical or digital, old or new, do this.\", \"from\": 1235, \"to\": 1436, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"My paper on Rules and Standards for Software Platforms shows that most sophisticated software platforms have and enforce rules and standards for developers.\", \"from\": 1437, \"to\": 1593, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Not-for-profit platforms are another source of ideas on governance for virtual currencies.\", \"from\": 1594, \"to\": 1684, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"My HBR blog post with Dick Schmalensee describes many of these.\", \"from\": 1685, \"to\": 1748, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Interesting, standard setting organizations, which have been responsible for laying the foundations for many important technologies, typically have supermajority voting, often requiring 70 percent of more of the votes.\", \"from\": 1749, \"to\": 1967, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Do not forget the sunblock.\", \"from\": 1969, \"to\": 1996, \"entities\": []}]}"